A letter from a gentleman of worth from Dublin in Ireland, to a friend in London. Wherein is declared a famous victory obtained against the rebels in Ireland, very lately by Colonell Muncke. With other good service done by others in other places; also neer about Dublin, and in the pale. J. B.
7, [1] p.
Printed for R. B., London : Jan. 7. 1642 [i.e. 1643]
Signed: J.B. Dublin, 21 Decemb., 1642. Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
